TOY GAME ENGINE WITH TS+ZIG/WASM/WEBGPU
=======================================

This project was to vibe a ts -> wasm/zig -> webgpu pipeline with claude code.

The initial step was to have a wasm module that calculates two numbers and logs to console.

npm run clean
npm run build
npm run verify
npm run dev
 -> open https://localhost:5173/ (and https://localhost:5173/scene.html)



INITIAL WASM CHECK
------------------

TO RUN:

npm run build:wasm
cp game_engine.wasm public/
npm run dev




brew install zig
zig version
  0.15.1

export fn add(a: i32, b: i32) i32 {
    return a + b;
}

<!-- zig build-lib -target wasm32-freestanding -dynamic life.zig -O ReleaseSmall -->
<!-- https://ziggit.dev/t/zig-webassembly/2550/2 -->
zig build-exe ./wasm_module.zig -target wasm32-freestanding -fno-entry -rdynamic

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <body>
    <h1>Wasm + Zig Test</h1>
    <script type="module">
      // const wasm = await WebAssembly.instantiateStreaming(fetch("life.wasm"));
      const wasm = await WebAssembly.instantiateStreaming(fetch("life.a"));
      console.log("2 + 3 =", wasm.instance.exports.add(2, 3));
    </script>
  </body>
</html>

python3 -m http.server 8080




CLAUDE CODE SETUP WITH LiteLLM PROXY
====================================

- check teh environment variables in .env
- source cc.sh to start


